description.p:
Accordingly, the present invention provides a method of processing one or more blades of a row of blades which forms part of a rotor for a gas turbine engine, the method including:
providing a rotor disc having a slot for mounting one or more blades;
applying tape at one or both sides of the slot such that when the blades are loaded in the slot the tape reduces a range of tilt angles which can be adopted by the blades;
loading the blades in the slot; and
performing a processing operation on the loaded blades.

Embodiments of the invention will now be described by way of example with reference to the accompanying drawings in which:
Figure 1 shows a longitudinal cross-section through a ducted fan gas turbine engine;
Figure 2 shows a typical abradable liner tip rub profile;
Figure 3 shows an axial root blade on the left and circumferential root blade on the right;
Figure 4 shows schematically three tilt positions in which a blade can rest relative to a disc;
Figure 5 shows schematically (a) a ground profile of two blades resting in two positions during the grinding process, and (b) the ground blades with resting positions swapped during a period of use;
Figure 6 shows schematically a rearwards directed view of blade tip of a blade with an axial root for different levels of tilt;
Figure 7 shows schematically (a) a blade loaded in a circumferential slot of a disc and set at its nominal location, (b) shows the blade in the same slot but tilted to its maximum rearward location, (c) the same disc, but now with tape applied along the edges of the slot, (d) the blade loaded in the slot of the taped disc and set at its nominal location, and (e) the blade in the slot of the taped disc and tilted to its now reduced maximum rearward location;
Figure 8 shows respective distributions for the manufacturing tolerances of a blade and a disc, the horizontal distance between the two dashed vertical lines at the centres of the two distributions indicating a nominal radial clearance between the underside of the blade platform and the rim of the disc when the blade is centrifuged outwardly in its zero tilt location; and
Figure 9 shows schematically a blade loaded in an axial slot of a disc, with tape applied at the mouth of the slot.

claim.claim-text:
A method of processing one or more blades of a row of blades (500, 510) which forms part of a rotor for a gas turbine engine, the method including:
providing a rotor disc (504, 514) having a slot (502, 512) for mounting one or more blades;
applying tape (506, 516) at one or both sides of the slot such that when the blades are loaded in the slot the tape reduces the range of tilt angles which can be adopted by the blades;
loading the blades in the slot;
performing a processing operation on the loaded blades; and
removing the tape from the disc after the processing operation.
